OS_BinaryToDecimal  (&28)
#Parent OS_
=>	R0 =	integer
	R1 =	pointer to buffer
	R2 =	size of buffer
<=	R2 =	length of string

This SWI converts a 32 bit integer to a string, much like <OS_ConvertInteger4=>OS_Convert>, except that no terminating 0 byte is placed at the end.
#Line
See <PRM 1, page 456=>PRM-1:456>.
